---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout active="faq.html" footerTagline="Your LOCAL source for secure, mouse-proof storage containers serving the Uintah Basin! 📦🏔️">
  <Fragment slot="head">
  <!-- ═══ PILLAR 3: TITLE TAG ═══ -->
  <title>Storage FAQ Vernal UT | Fort Knox Self Storage</title>

  <!-- ═══ PILLAR 3: META DESCRIPTION ═══ -->
  <meta name="description" content="Answers to the most common questions about self storage in Vernal, Utah. Prices, unit sizes, 24/7 access, mouse-proof containers, RV parking & more. Call 435-828-7710.">

  <!-- Location Meta -->
  <meta name="geo.region" content="US-UT">
  <meta name="geo.placename" content="Vernal">
  <meta name="geo.position" content="40.4555;-109.5287">

  <!-- Open Graph -->
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:title" content="Storage FAQ Vernal UT | Fort Knox Self Storage">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Common questions about self storage in Vernal, Utah — prices, sizes, 24/7 access, mouse-proof containers, RV parking. Call James: 435-828-7710.">
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://vernalfortknoxselfstorage.com/pictures/fortknoxlogo.webp">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://vernalfortknoxselfstorage.com/faq.html">

  <!-- Canonical -->
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://vernalfortknoxselfstorage.com/faq.html">

  <!-- ═══ PILLAR 4: FAQPage Schema ═══ -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@graph": [
      {
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "@id": "https://vernalfortknoxselfstorage.com/faq.html",
        "url": "https://vernalfortknoxselfstorage.com/faq.html",
        "name": "Storage FAQ — Fort Knox Self Storage Vernal Utah",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How much does storage cost in Vernal, Utah?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Fort Knox Self Storage offers 20-foot mouse-proof containers starting at $130/month and 40-foot containers at $230/month. No hidden fees. New customers signing a 6-month contract receive the first 2 months completely free. Call James at 435-828-7710."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is included in the monthly price?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "The monthly rate includes 24/7 access, fire detection monitoring, and use of your steel container. There are no admin fees, lock fees, or move-in fees. Price quoted is price charged."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I get the first 2 months free?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Sign a 6-month rental agreement and your first two months are free. Call James at 435-828-7710 to get started — move-in can happen the same day."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What size storage unit do I need?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "A 20-foot container holds the contents of a typical 1-2 bedroom apartment — furniture, boxes, and appliances. A 40-foot container holds a full home and garage, including large equipment and vehicles. Call James at 435-828-7710 for a personalized recommendation."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Are the containers really mouse-proof and fireproof?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Fort Knox uses all-steel shipping containers — fully sealed with no wood framing, gaps, or entry points for rodents or pests. All units include 24/7 fire detection alerts. This is the key difference from traditional wood-frame storage buildings used by most Vernal storage facilities."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I access my storage unit at any hour?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Fort Knox provides 24/7 access with your personal access code — no restricted hours, no holidays off. This is especially convenient for oil field workers and contractors in the Uintah Basin on irregular schedules."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Where is Fort Knox Self Storage located?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Fort Knox Self Storage is at 2225 South 3250 East, Vernal, Utah 84078 — just south of Naples. Convenient for residents across Vernal, Jensen, Naples, Roosevelt, and all of Uintah County."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Do you offer RV, boat, or vehicle parking?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Fort Knox offers outdoor parking spaces for cars, trucks, RVs, boats, campers, and motorhomes. Call James at 435-828-7710 for current availability and monthly pricing."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I store oil field tools or contractor equipment?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Many Fort Knox customers use 40-foot containers for tools, equipment, and business inventory. 24/7 access and steel construction make it the top choice for Uintah Basin oil field workers and tradespeople."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I start renting a storage unit at Fort Knox?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Call James at 435-828-7710 or stop by 2225 South 3250 East, Vernal UT. Choose your size, sign a simple rental agreement, get your 24/7 access code, and move in the same day."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
        "itemListElement": [
          { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://vernalfortknoxselfstorage.com/" },
          { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "FAQ", "item": "https://vernalfortknoxselfstorage.com/faq.html" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "@type": "WebPage",
        "speakable": {
          "@type": "SpeakableSpecification",
          "cssSelector": [".page-summary", ".faq-hero-answer", "h1"]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <style>
    /* ═══ FAQ Hero — shorter than homepage hero ═══ */
    .faq-hero {
      position: relative;
      background: #8B4513 url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/dark-wood.png');
      background-size: 500px;
      color: var(--white);
      padding: 80px 0 60px;
      overflow: hidden;
      border-top: 8px solid var(--metal-dark);
      border-bottom: 8px solid var(--metal-dark);
      box-shadow:
        inset 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.6),
        inset 0 -8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
      text-align: center;
    }
    .faq-hero::before {
      content: '⭐';
      position: absolute;
      top: 30px; left: 40px;
      font-size: 4rem;
      color: var(--accent-color);
      opacity: 0.4;
      text-shadow: 3px 3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
    }
    .faq-hero::after {
      content: '⭐';
      position: absolute;
      top: 30px; right: 40px;
      font-size: 4rem;
      color: var(--accent-color);
      opacity: 0.4;
      text-shadow: 3px 3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
    }
    .faq-hero-inner {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
      animation: fadeInUp 0.8s ease;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    /* Breadcrumb */
    .breadcrumb {
      font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .breadcrumb a {
      color: var(--accent-color);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .breadcrumb a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .breadcrumb span { margin: 0 6px; }

    /* ═══ Page Summary Block ═══ */
    .page-summary-wrap {
      background: rgba(218,165,32,0.15);
      border-left: 5px solid var(--accent-color);
      padding: 16px 22px;
      margin: 24px auto 0;
      border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      max-width: 700px;
      text-align: left;
    }
    .page-summary {
      font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--white);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .page-summary a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: underline; }
    .page-summary-meta {
      font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      margin-top: 6px;
      display: block;
    }

    /* ═══ FAQ BODY SECTION ═══ */
    .faq-body {
      padding: 70px 0 80px;
      background: #F5DEB3 url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/light-wool.png');
    }
    .faq-body .container {
      max-width: 900px;
    }

    /* Category header */
    .faq-category {
      margin-bottom: 44px;
    }
    .faq-category-title {
      font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
      font-size: 1.55rem;
      font-weight: 900;
      color: var(--primary-dark);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      border-bottom: 4px solid var(--accent-color);
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
    }
    .faq-category-title .cat-icon {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    /* ═══ Accordion — styled rustic to match site ═══ */
    .faq-accordion details {
      background: #FFF8DC url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/wood-pattern.png');
      background-size: 400px;
      border: 3px solid var(--primary-dark);
      border-radius: 6px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
      transition: border-color 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .faq-accordion details[open] {
      border-color: var(--accent-color);
      box-shadow:
        0 0 0 2px rgba(218,165,32,0.3),
        var(--shadow-md);
    }
    .faq-accordion summary {
      padding: 18px 56px 18px 22px;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--primary-dark);
      list-style: none;
      position: relative;
      line-height: 1.45;
      user-select: none;
    }
    .faq-accordion summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
    .faq-accordion summary::after {
      content: '+';
      position: absolute;
      right: 18px;
      top: 50%;
      transform: translateY(-50%);
      width: 28px;
      height: 28px;
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: var(--primary-dark);
      border-radius: 50%;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      font-weight: 300;
      line-height: 1;
      text-align: center;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, background 0.3s ease;
    }
    /* Flex trick: position the pseudo-element as flex child not possible, use grid instead */
    .faq-accordion details[open] summary::after {
      content: '−';
      background: var(--primary-dark);
      color: var(--accent-color);
    }
    .faq-accordion summary:hover {
      background: rgba(218,165,32,0.08);
    }
    .faq-answer {
      padding: 0 22px 20px 22px;
      font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
      color: var(--text-dark);
      border-top: 2px dashed rgba(101,67,33,0.25);
      padding-top: 16px;
    }
    .faq-answer p { margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .faq-answer p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .faq-answer a {
      color: var(--primary-dark);
      font-weight: 700;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    .faq-answer a:hover { color: var(--accent-color); }
    .faq-answer strong { color: var(--primary-dark); }
    .faq-answer .answer-cta {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 10px;
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: var(--primary-dark);
      font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      padding: 8px 18px;
      border-radius: 30px;
      border: 2px solid var(--primary-dark);
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: all 0.2s ease;
    }
    .faq-answer .answer-cta:hover {
      background: var(--primary-dark);
      color: var(--accent-color);
    }

    /* ═══ Still Have Questions CTA Block ═══ */
    .faq-cta-block {
      background: #CD853F url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/wood-pattern.png');
      background-size: 350px;
      border: 6px solid var(--primary-dark);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 40px 36px;
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 52px;
      box-shadow:
        inset 0 0 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2),
        var(--shadow-md);
    }
    .faq-cta-block h2 {
      font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
      font-size: 2rem;
      color: var(--metal-dark);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      text-shadow: 1px 1px 3px rgba(218,165,32,0.5);
    }
    .faq-cta-block p {
      font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--metal-dark);
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .faq-cta-block .btn {
      animation: buttonFlash 1.5s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
    .faq-cta-block .btn:hover { animation: none; }

    /* ═══ Mobile ═══ */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .faq-hero { padding: 60px 0 40px; }
      .faq-hero::before, .faq-hero::after { font-size: 2.5rem; }
      .faq-hero-inner h1 { font-size: 1.4rem !important; letter-spacing: 1px; }
      .faq-category-title { font-size: 1.2rem; }
      .faq-accordion summary { font-size: 0.93rem; padding: 16px 50px 16px 16px; }
      .faq-answer { padding: 14px 16px 18px; font-size: 0.9rem; }
      .faq-cta-block { padding: 28px 20px; }
      .faq-cta-block h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    }
  </style>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- ═══ FAQ HERO ═══ -->
  <section class="faq-hero" aria-label="FAQ page header">
    <div class="faq-hero-inner">

      <!-- Breadcrumb — helps Google understand page structure -->
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="index.html">Home</a>
        <span>›</span>
        <span>FAQ</span>
      </nav>

      <!-- PILLAR 3: H1 — one per page, includes primary keyword -->
      <h1 class="hero-title" style="font-size: 2rem; letter-spacing: 2px;">
        Frequently Asked Questions<br>
        <span style="font-size: 1.2rem; letter-spacing: 1px; font-weight: 400; text-transform: none; font-style: italic;">Storage Units in Vernal, Utah</span>
      </h1>

      <!-- PILLAR 3: PAGE SUMMARY BLOCK — AI crawlers prioritize this -->
      <div class="page-summary-wrap" role="note" aria-label="Page summary">
        <p class="page-summary">
          <strong>Fort Knox Self Storage</strong> answers the most common questions about self storage in <strong>Vernal, Utah</strong>.
          20ft containers from <strong>$130/month</strong> · 40ft from <strong>$230/month</strong> · 24/7 access · mouse-proof steel containers.
          Located at <strong>2225 South 3250 East, Vernal UT 84078</strong>.
          Call <a href="tel:4358287710">James at 435-828-7710</a> to reserve today.
        </p>
        <span class="page-summary-meta">Last updated: <time datetime="2026-02-01">February 2026</time></span>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══ FAQ BODY ═══ -->
  <section class="faq-body" aria-labelledby="faq-main-heading">
    <div class="container">

      <h2 id="faq-main-heading" class="section-title" style="margin-bottom: 50px;">
        Your Questions, Answered
      </h2>


      <!-- ─── CATEGORY 1: PRICING & CONTRACTS ─── -->
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-category-title">
          <span class="cat-icon">💰</span> Pricing &amp; Contracts
        </h3>

        <div class="faq-accordion">

          <details open>
            <summary>How much does storage cost in Vernal, Utah?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Fort Knox Self Storage offers the most competitive rates in the Uintah Basin:</p>
              <p>
                <strong>20-foot container — $130/month</strong><br>
                Holds a typical 1–2 bedroom apartment's worth of furniture, boxes, and appliances.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>40-foot container — $230/month</strong><br>
                Holds a full home and garage, including large equipment, vehicles, and business inventory.
              </p>
              <p>New customers signing a 6-month agreement receive the <strong>first 2 months completely free</strong>. No hidden fees, ever.</p>
              <a href="tel:4358287710" class="answer-cta">📞 Call James: 435-828-7710</a>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Are there any hidden fees or move-in charges?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>None. The monthly rate you're quoted is the monthly rate you pay. There are no admin fees, no lock fees, no move-in fees, and no surprise charges on your first bill. Fort Knox is proud of its no-hidden-fees policy — it's one of the reasons customers stay long-term.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>How do I get the first 2 months free?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>It's simple: sign a 6-month rental agreement and your first two months are free. Call <a href="tel:4358287710">James at 435-828-7710</a> — he can set up your agreement the same day you want to move in. This offer applies to new customers on both 20ft and 40ft units.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you offer month-to-month rentals?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes. Fort Knox offers flexible month-to-month rentals as well as the 6-month agreement (which includes the 2 free months promotion). Call <a href="tel:4358287710">James at 435-828-7710</a> to discuss which option works best for your situation.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you offer discounts for long-term renters or oil field contractors?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>James works with many oil field workers and contractors in the Uintah Basin. Call <a href="tel:4358287710">435-828-7710</a> directly to discuss long-term arrangements — because Fort Knox is locally owned, there's flexibility that a national chain can't offer.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- ─── CATEGORY 2: UNIT SIZES ─── -->
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-category-title">
          <span class="cat-icon">📦</span> Storage Unit Sizes
        </h3>

        <div class="faq-accordion">

          <details>
            <summary>What size storage unit do I need?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p><strong>20-foot container</strong> — best for a 1–2 bedroom apartment. Fits full furniture sets, boxes, appliances, a washer/dryer, and a bike or two. Roughly 160 sq ft of floor space.</p>
              <p><strong>40-foot container</strong> — best for a 3–4 bedroom home or a home plus a garage. Fits sofas, dining sets, bedroom sets, large appliances, lawn equipment, tools, and more. Roughly 320 sq ft of floor space.</p>
              <p>Not sure? Call <a href="tel:4358287710">James at 435-828-7710</a> — he'll ask a few quick questions and point you to the right size.</p>
              <a href="container-sales.html" class="answer-cta">View Container Details →</a>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can I use a container to store business inventory or equipment?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Absolutely. Many Fort Knox customers use 40-foot containers as business storage — tools, equipment, inventory, and contractor supplies. The steel construction is weather-tight, rodent-proof, and the 24/7 access fits any work schedule. Popular with oil field workers, plumbers, electricians, and landscapers throughout Vernal and the Uintah Basin.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can I store a vehicle inside a container?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>A standard car or small truck can fit inside a 40-foot container, though this limits the space available for other items. For vehicle storage, Fort Knox also offers <a href="parking.html">outdoor parking spaces</a> for cars, trucks, RVs, boats, and campers — often a more practical option. Call <a href="tel:4358287710">James at 435-828-7710</a> for availability.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you sell shipping containers in Vernal?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes! Fort Knox also sells 20ft and 40ft shipping containers. Whether you need one for storage on your property, a job site, or another use, contact James to check current inventory and pricing.</p>
              <a href="container-sales.html" class="answer-cta">Container Sales Info →</a>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- ─── CATEGORY 3: SECURITY & PROTECTION ─── -->
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-category-title">
          <span class="cat-icon">🔒</span> Security &amp; Protection
        </h3>

        <div class="faq-accordion">

          <details>
            <summary>Are the storage containers really mouse-proof?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes — and this is the #1 reason Vernal residents choose Fort Knox. Fort Knox uses all-steel shipping containers with no wood framing, no drywall, and no gaps. Unlike traditional storage buildings throughout Uintah County where mice, rats, and insects are a known problem, Fort Knox containers are fully sealed steel. There is simply no entry point for rodents or pests.</p>
              <p>This makes Fort Knox the safest choice for storing furniture, clothing, electronics, documents, and anything else that can be damaged by pests.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What fire protection is in place?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Every unit at Fort Knox has 24/7 fire detection alerts. Unlike most Vernal storage facilities, which have limited or no fire monitoring, Fort Knox steel containers are also inherently fire-resistant — steel does not burn. The fire detection system alerts management immediately, day or night.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>How is my unit protected against theft?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Each renter receives a personal access code — only you can access your unit. The facility is gated and well-lit. As a locally-owned business, James is on-call 24/7 and personally monitors the property. Steel containers are also significantly harder to break into than standard storage units with roll-up doors.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Are the containers spider-proof too?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes. The all-steel sealed construction that makes the containers mouse-proof also keeps spiders and other insects out. This is another common concern in rural Utah that Fort Knox solves simply by using steel shipping containers instead of wood-frame buildings.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- ─── CATEGORY 4: ACCESS & HOURS ─── -->
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-category-title">
          <span class="cat-icon">🕐</span> Access &amp; Hours
        </h3>

        <div class="faq-accordion">

          <details>
            <summary>Can I access my unit at any hour, including nights and holidays?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes — 24/7, 365 days a year. Fort Knox has no restricted access hours. You'll receive a personal code that unlocks the facility at any time of day or night. This is especially important for oil field workers, CDL drivers, and contractors in the Uintah Basin whose schedules don't follow a 9-to-5.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What hours is the office or manager available?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>James Richards, the owner and manager, is available 24/7 by phone at <a href="tel:4358287710">435-828-7710</a>. Because Fort Knox is locally owned, you're always calling the actual owner — not a corporate call center. James can answer questions, set up rentals, and handle any concerns at any hour.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details>
